g Mountain, Namibia -- t12. Emergence of Cultural Tourism in Southern Africa: Case Studies of Two Communities in Botswana -- t13. Cultural Tourism in Southern Africa: Progress, Opportunities and Challenges -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThis volume provides an accessible overview of cultural tourism in southern Africa. It examines the utilisation of culture in southern African tourism and the related impacts, possibilities and challenges from deep and wide-ranging perspectives. The chapters use case studies to showcase some of the cultural tourism which occurs in the region and link to concepts such as authenticity, commodification, the tourist gaze and ‘Otherness’, heritage, sustainability and sustainable livelihoods. The authors scrutinise both positive and negative impacts of cultural tourism throughout the book and explore issues including the definition of community, ethical considerations, empowerment, gender, participation and inequality. The book will be a useful resource for students and researchers of tourism, geography, anthropology and cultural studies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aHeritage tourismzAfrica, Southern. 4aCultural studies. 4aGEOGRAPHY. 4aTourism industry. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Industries / Hospitality, Travel & Tourism.2bisacsh  aAuthenticity.  aCommodification.  aCultural tourism.  aEthnicity.  aHeritage tourism.  aOtherness.  aSustainability.  aSustainable livelihoods.  aTourist gaze.1 aButler, Gareth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIvanovic, Milena, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLapeyre, Renaud, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLenao, Monkgogi, econtributor.4